Remove volume from a 3-dimensional shape such that a wall of the
provided thickness remains, taking volume starting at the providedface, leaving it open in that direction.

```kcl
shell(
  @solids: [[Solid; 1+]](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-Solid),
  thickness: number(Length),
  faces: [[tag; 1+]](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-tag),
): [[Solid]](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-Solid)
```


### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `solids` | [`[Solid; 1+]`](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-Solid) | Which solid (or solids) to shell out | Yes |
| `thickness` | `number(Length)` | The thickness of the shell | Yes |
| `faces` | [`[tag; 1+]`](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-tag) | The faces you want removed | Yes |

### Returns

[`[Solid]`](/docs/kcl/types/std-types-Solid)


### Examples

```kcl
// Remove the end face for the extrusion.
firstSketch = startSketchOn(XY)
    |> startProfile(at = [-12, 12])
    |> line(end = [24, 0])
    |> line(end = [0, -24])
    |> line(end = [-24, 0])
    |> close()
    |> extrude(length = 6)

// Remove the end face for the extrusion.
shell(
    firstSketch,
    faces = [END],
    thickness = 0.25,
)
```
